cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.SD 

This paper deals with the generation of socially-informed timelines, which involves natural language processing and information retrieval techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper also involves optimization techniques, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also deals with information retrieval and summarization, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of user-generated content, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
